The NHS as described by Nye Bevan:

to meet the needs of everyone; 
to be free at the point of delivery; 
to be based on clinical need, not ability to pay.

 "No society can legitimately call itself civilised if a sick person is denied medical aid because of lack of means."

Well, the reality is that this civilised nation's government is suffocating the NHS, and as a consequence, it is not able to meet the founding principles, instead offering trolleys in corridors for those who cannot pay.
